<subSubSection pageId="14" pageNumber="15" type="diagnosis">
<paragraph blockId="14.[151,1437,1321,2030]" pageId="14" pageNumber="15">
<emphasis bold="true" box="[199,321,1321,1346]" pageId="14" pageNumber="15">Diagnosis.</emphasis>
A moderately-sloped head and bicuspid teeth in the outer row of the jaws place this species in 
<taxonomicName authority="Stauffer, Bowers, Kellogg &amp; McKaye, 1997" authorityName="Stauffer, Bowers, Kellogg &amp; McKaye" authorityYear="1997" box="[151,289,1358,1382]" class="Teleostei" family="Cichlidae" genus="Metriaclima" higherTaxonomySource="GBIF" kingdom="Animalia" order="Perciformes" pageId="14" pageNumber="15" phylum="Chordata" rank="genus">
<emphasis box="[151,289,1358,1382]" italics="true" pageId="14" pageNumber="15">Metriaclima</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
. A black pelvic fin, a dark-blue cheek and preorbital area, and a blue dorsal fin without a black submarginal band in breeding males and the light-brown colored females that have yellow fin-margins distinguish 
<taxonomicName authority="Stauffer, Bowers, Kellogg &amp; McKaye, 1997" authorityName="Stauffer, Bowers, Kellogg &amp; McKaye" authorityYear="1997" class="Teleostei" family="Cichlidae" genus="Metriaclima" higherTaxonomySource="GBIF" kingdom="Animalia" order="Perciformes" pageId="14" pageNumber="15" phylum="Chordata" rank="species" species="sciasma">
<emphasis italics="true" pageId="14" pageNumber="15">M. sciasma</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
from all other members of 
<taxonomicName authority="Stauffer, Bowers, Kellogg &amp; McKaye, 1997" authorityName="Stauffer, Bowers, Kellogg &amp; McKaye" authorityYear="1997" box="[564,702,1430,1454]" class="Teleostei" family="Cichlidae" genus="Metriaclima" higherTaxonomySource="GBIF" kingdom="Animalia" order="Perciformes" pageId="14" pageNumber="15" phylum="Chordata" rank="genus">
<emphasis box="[564,702,1430,1454]" italics="true" pageId="14" pageNumber="15">Metriaclima</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
. Breeding males of 
<taxonomicName authority="Stauffer, Bowers, Kellogg &amp; McKaye, 1997" authorityName="Stauffer, Bowers, Kellogg &amp; McKaye" authorityYear="1997" box="[938,1068,1431,1454]" class="Teleostei" family="Cichlidae" genus="Metriaclima" higherTaxonomySource="GBIF" kingdom="Animalia" order="Perciformes" pageId="14" pageNumber="15" phylum="Chordata" rank="species" species="sciasma">
<emphasis box="[938,1068,1431,1454]" italics="true" pageId="14" pageNumber="15">M. sciasma</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
are distinguished from those of some populations of 
<taxonomicName box="[387,487,1466,1490]" class="Actinopterygii" family="Cichlidae" genus="Pseudotropheus" kingdom="Animalia" order="Perciformes" pageId="14" pageNumber="15" phylum="Chordata" rank="species" species="zebra">
<emphasis box="[387,487,1466,1490]" italics="true" pageId="14" pageNumber="15">M. zebra</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
by the presence of a single interorbital bar (
<quantity box="[987,1032,1465,1489]" metricMagnitude="-2" metricUnit="m" metricValue="5.08" pageId="14" pageNumber="15" unit="in" value="2.0">2 in</quantity>
<taxonomicName box="[1039,1139,1466,1490]" class="Actinopterygii" family="Cichlidae" genus="Pseudotropheus" kingdom="Animalia" order="Perciformes" pageId="14" pageNumber="15" phylum="Chordata" rank="species" species="zebra">
<emphasis box="[1039,1139,1466,1490]" italics="true" pageId="14" pageNumber="15">M. zebra</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
) and by black pigment on the anterior membranes of the anal fin. Female 
<taxonomicName authority="Stauffer, Bowers, Kellogg &amp; McKaye, 1997" authorityName="Stauffer, Bowers, Kellogg &amp; McKaye" authorityYear="1997" box="[702,832,1503,1526]" class="Teleostei" family="Cichlidae" genus="Metriaclima" higherTaxonomySource="GBIF" kingdom="Animalia" order="Perciformes" pageId="14" pageNumber="15" phylum="Chordata" rank="species" species="sciasma">
<emphasis box="[702,832,1503,1526]" italics="true" pageId="14" pageNumber="15">M. sciasma</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
cannot reliably be distinguished from those of most other members of the 
<taxonomicName authority="Stauffer, Bowers, Kellogg &amp; McKaye, 1997" authorityName="Stauffer, Bowers, Kellogg &amp; McKaye" authorityYear="1997" box="[400,479,1538,1562]" class="Teleostei" family="Cichlidae" genus="Metriaclima" higherTaxonomySource="GBIF" kingdom="Animalia" order="Perciformes" pageId="14" pageNumber="23" phylum="Chordata" rank="species" species="aurora">Aurora</taxonomicName>
group, but differ from those of 
<taxonomicName authority="Stauffer, Bowers, Kellogg &amp; McKaye, 1997" authorityName="Stauffer, Bowers, Kellogg &amp; McKaye" authorityYear="1997" box="[840,955,1539,1562]" class="Teleostei" family="Cichlidae" genus="Metriaclima" higherTaxonomySource="GBIF" kingdom="Animalia" order="Perciformes" pageId="14" pageNumber="15" phylum="Chordata" rank="species" species="aurora">
<emphasis box="[840,955,1539,1562]" italics="true" pageId="14" pageNumber="15">M. aurora</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
by more vertical bars below the dorsal fin (
<number box="[159,216,1574,1598]" pageId="14" pageNumber="15" value="8.5" valueMax="10.0" valueMin="7.0">7–10</number>
vs. 
<number box="[262,278,1574,1598]" pageId="14" pageNumber="15" value="6.0">6</number>
).
</paragraph>
</subSubSection>
<subSubSection lastPageId="16" lastPageNumber="17" pageId="14" pageNumber="15" type="description">
<paragraph blockId="14.[151,1437,1321,2030]" pageId="14" pageNumber="15">
<emphasis bold="true" box="[199,345,1609,1634]" pageId="14" pageNumber="15">Description.</emphasis>
Morphometric and meristic data in 
<tableCitation box="[768,857,1609,1633]" captionStart="TABLE 5" captionStartId="15.[151,235,152,173]" captionTargetBox="[151,1435,274,1990]" captionTargetPageId="15" captionText="TABLE 5. Morphometric and meristic values of Metriaclima sciasma from Magunga, Makonde, and Ngwazi. Holotype from Magunga." httpUri="http://table.plazi.org/id/DF6D75B40D7B83699DEFFF1BFF35FF32" pageId="14" pageNumber="15" tableUuid="DF6D75B40D7B83699DEFFF1BFF35FF32">
Table 
<number box="[841,857,1609,1633]" pageId="14" pageNumber="15" value="5.0">5</number>
</tableCitation>
. Dorsal snout profile slightly concave to straight; mouth cleft with slightly downward angle; jaws isognathous. Teeth on dentary in two to three rows, on premaxilla in two to four rows; outer row teeth typically bicuspid anteriorly and unicuspid posteriorly, inner rows tricuspid, innermost row unicuspid; lower pharyngeal jaw with numerous slender teeth with teeth in posterior row slightly larger. Portion of upper dental arcade normally visible in closed mouth. Tips of teeth in premaxilla and dentary in V-shaped line with anteriormost in upper and lower jaw furthest apart and separate in closed mouth. Lateral scales ctenoid.
</paragraph>
<paragraph blockId="14.[151,1437,1321,2030]" pageId="14" pageNumber="15">
Lateral body coloration of breeding males blue dorsally with 
<number box="[907,963,1862,1886]" pageId="14" pageNumber="15" value="8.5" valueMax="10.0" valueMin="7.0">7–10</number>
gray bars, white ventrally, and blue/gray caudal peduncle. Preorbital, cheek, and operculum dark blue/gray; blue opercular spot; gray/blue gular region; premaxillary and maxillary blue/gray; blue/gray interorbital bar. Dorsal fin blue with light-blue lappets. Caudal fin with gray rays and blue membranes. Anal fin blue/gray with 
<number box="[835,877,1969,1993]" pageId="14" pageNumber="15" value="4.5" valueMax="7.0" valueMin="2.0">2–7</number>
yellow ocelli. Pelvic fin black with white leading edge. Pectoral fin clear.
</paragraph>
<caption ID-Table-UUID="DF6D75B40D7B83699DEFFF1BFF35FF32" httpUri="http://table.plazi.org/id/DF6D75B40D7B83699DEFFF1BFF35FF32" pageId="15" pageNumber="16" targetBox="[151,1435,274,1990]" targetIsTable="true" targetPageId="15">
<paragraph blockId="15.[151,1435,152,254]" pageId="15" pageNumber="16">
<emphasis bold="true" box="[151,261,152,173]" pageId="15" pageNumber="16">TABLE 5.</emphasis>
Morphometric and meristic values of 
<taxonomicName authority="Stauffer, Bowers, Kellogg &amp; McKaye, 1997" authorityName="Stauffer, Bowers, Kellogg &amp; McKaye" authorityYear="1997" box="[654,868,152,174]" class="Teleostei" family="Cichlidae" genus="Metriaclima" higherTaxonomySource="GBIF" kingdom="Animalia" order="Perciformes" pageId="15" pageNumber="16" phylum="Chordata" rank="species" species="sciasma">
<emphasis box="[654,868,152,174]" italics="true" pageId="15" pageNumber="16">Metriaclima sciasma</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
from Magunga, Makonde, and Ngwazi. Holotype from Magunga.
</paragraph>
</caption>
<paragraph blockId="15.[151,1435,152,254]" lastBlockId="16.[151,1437,151,463]" lastPageId="16" lastPageNumber="17" pageId="15" pageNumber="16">
all Magunga Makonde Ngwazi Females brown dorsally and gray/white ventrally. Head brown with blue highlights on operculum and grey/ green opercular spot; white gular region. Dorsal and anal fins yellow/brown. Proximal third of caudal fin dark brown, distal third light brown/yellow, membranes with faint blue spots. Pelvic fin with white leading edge, first 
<number box="[1422,1436,223,247]" pageId="16" pageNumber="17" value="2.0">2</number>
rays and membranes yellow/brown with remaining clear. Pectoral fin clear.
</paragraph>
</subSubSection>
